cast.text:
To be eligible for First Draft Club's January’s $500 prize pool, members must share new, original writing in /firstdraft at least 3 of the 4 weeks this month.

Weeks end on Sundays: January 5, 12, 19, and 26.

There’s no topic, length, or format requirement—your writing can be a @paragraph post, a screenshot of your Apple Notes, or even just a long cast.

It also doesn't need to be "finished"! The point of @firstdraftclub is just showing up and sharing something :)

The only requirement is posting in /firstdraft by Sunday to count for the week. New members can join anytime but must meet the 3-week threshold in January to qualify.

show_title: GM Farcaster ep209 Friday January 31, 2025 with @markfishman  /firstdraft
text:
A year ago today, Read Write Own was released. So much has happened in crypto since then.

The past year, I spent a lot of time traveling and speaking at events—some crypto-focused, some not. Even as crypto faced regulatory uncertainty in Washington and sustained criticism from mainstream media, I kept hearing something different from the people I met: passion and optimism. There was a clear gap between the narrative out there and what I was seeing on the ground.

So, while I’m excited to see the tides turn with growing bipartisan and institutional support, I’m not entirely surprised. Crypto was never going away. At some point, the value of what blockchains enable—stablecoins, DeFi, AI systems, games, social experiences, and more—had to be recognized. We’re still far from the full vision I described in Read Write Own, but we’re moving forward. 

Huge thanks to all the founders, builders, and supporters who tuned out the noise and kept building. Onward.

text:
GN Degens,

Bans Update

We're applying bans as we wrap up Season 12. In Season 13, all bans will be reset, giving everyone a fresh opportunity to earn tips.

At the end of each season, we'll reevaluate activity using a rule-based analysis of our choosing to weed out behavior that closely aligns with farming. To prevent gaming the system, we won't announce rules in advance but will use various techniques to monitor how tips are being distributed.
